WEBVTT

00:01.066 --> 00:02.300
Can you please explain to me

00:02.367 --> 00:04.467
why we keep volunteering
for the dance committee

00:04.533 --> 00:06.867
when we know Kate's gonna be
put in charge?

00:06.934 --> 00:09.133
I don't know,
I'm just here for the free food.

00:09.600 --> 00:12.533
Gordo, there is no free food here.

00:15.133 --> 00:17.367
You're right. See ya!

00:17.467 --> 00:19.266
-[WHOOSHES]
-[BOTH SCOFF]

00:20.400 --> 00:23.033
Well, I know that I'm here because
being on the dance committee,

00:23.100 --> 00:25.567
it gives us an excuse
to go to the dance without dates.

00:25.633 --> 00:27.233
Who says we can't get dates?

00:28.567 --> 00:31.500
Fine, just as long as we don't end up
on the clean-up crew again.

00:31.567 --> 00:32.700
Ugh.

00:33.100 --> 00:35.100
The problem isn't
that I don't have a date,

00:35.166 --> 00:37.533
it's just that Josh Hartnett
doesn't go to this school.

00:39.700 --> 00:44.300
Well, I'm sure you're all extremely
excited about the Spring Fling Dance.

00:45.033 --> 00:48.500
You know, putting together
a good dance committee is a...

00:48.567 --> 00:53.400
It's a delicate balance involving
matching personalities and abilities.

00:53.467 --> 00:54.433
However, I have a meeting.

00:54.500 --> 00:57.033
So, Kate, you're in charge
of the decorations.

00:57.100 --> 00:58.166
Miranda, you cover the food,

00:58.233 --> 01:00.767
and, you, kid with the face,
you handle the music.

01:00.834 --> 01:03.200
Naturally, he picked me
for the decorations.

01:03.266 --> 01:05.200
That's the most important part.

01:05.266 --> 01:06.266
[MOUTHING] "Most important part."

01:07.367 --> 01:08.934
[MOCKING]
"That's the most important part."

01:10.767 --> 01:13.767
You know, you're right, Kate.
Decorations are a big deal.

01:14.200 --> 01:15.400
You and Lizzie are in charge.

01:16.767 --> 01:17.934
[CHUCKLES WRYLY]

01:18.000 --> 01:20.200
Decorations are
the most important part.

01:20.300 --> 01:22.433
[THEME SONG PLAYING]

02:02.567 --> 02:05.633
Mom, what do you think
about this table decoration?

02:05.700 --> 02:08.800
I think they'd better not be
from my garden.

02:08.867 --> 02:13.266
But, Mom, the Spring Fling decorations
are really, really important.

02:13.333 --> 02:14.367
I mean, if I bomb this,

02:14.433 --> 02:16.033
I'm gonna be known
as the girl who messed up

02:16.100 --> 02:17.100
the whole entire dance.

02:17.166 --> 02:19.000
And then, I'll end up a mathlete.

02:19.800 --> 02:21.500
Hey, I was a mathlete.

02:26.533 --> 02:28.033
Take all the flowers you need, honey.

02:28.100 --> 02:29.100
Thanks, Mom.

02:32.166 --> 02:34.233
So, you know, you were like,

02:34.300 --> 02:35.300
"Why are you mad at me?"

02:35.367 --> 02:38.467
And she was like,
"Because you never let me talk."

02:38.533 --> 02:42.734
You gotta admit, Lanny, you do tend
to dominate the conversation.

02:55.066 --> 02:58.100
The BMX Tornado Rider.

02:59.333 --> 03:03.934
You're right, Lanny.
It's bike time, big time.

03:06.667 --> 03:08.967
Okay, minor change to the dance theme.

03:09.066 --> 03:11.967
Instead of a Spring Fling,
it's Fashion Week in Paris.

03:12.033 --> 03:14.266
Uh, the school already voted, Kate.

03:14.367 --> 03:16.533
Uh, fine, we'll compromise.

03:16.600 --> 03:17.934
Springtime in Paris.

03:18.000 --> 03:20.300
I say we put
the Eiffel Towerover here,

03:20.367 --> 03:22.166
and people can enter
from over there

03:22.233 --> 03:24.800
under a huge canopy of yellow roses.

03:24.867 --> 03:26.000
No, pink.

03:26.066 --> 03:27.533
No, yellow.

03:27.600 --> 03:30.767
Uh, no, daisies.
Roses are so expensive.

03:30.834 --> 03:32.433
Think "Paris in the spring," Lizzie!

03:32.500 --> 03:34.433
Think "Let's stay on the budget,"
Kate.

03:34.500 --> 03:37.233
Think twice
before volunteering for anything.

03:37.300 --> 03:39.734
And we're gonna have
to get rid of Principal Baldy here.

03:39.800 --> 03:41.333
But where will the pigeons sit?

03:41.400 --> 03:43.567
"Walter Patterson.
Our first principal."

03:43.633 --> 03:45.400
"Hey you kids, cut that out!"

03:45.467 --> 03:47.467
Whatever. It's a bird toilet

03:47.533 --> 03:49.467
and it's interfering
with my romance vibe.

03:49.533 --> 03:50.700
Let's move it behind those bushes.

03:50.767 --> 03:52.834
Huh? No! Kate, wait! No!

03:55.333 --> 03:58.800
-Oops. Well, problem solved.
-But...

03:58.867 --> 04:02.200
Beheading the school principal
does not solve problems,

04:02.266 --> 04:03.633
it causes them!

04:03.700 --> 04:04.967
Kate, look at what you did.

04:05.033 --> 04:06.266
You're gonna be in so much trouble.

04:06.333 --> 04:08.433
Fine, I'll fix it.

04:14.734 --> 04:15.734
There. Perfect.

04:18.066 --> 04:19.600
-[GASPS]
-Oh, well!

04:19.667 --> 04:21.700
But, Kate, the statue.

04:21.767 --> 04:22.767
You're not gonna tell anyone,

04:22.834 --> 04:24.734
he's not gonna tell anyone,
case closed.

04:29.266 --> 04:31.700
-[GASPS LOUDLY]
-Hey, you kids, cut that out!

04:32.867 --> 04:36.533
Hey, Dad, how can we make
a whole bunch of money really quick?

04:36.600 --> 04:39.266
What do you need
a whole bunch of money for, honey?

04:39.333 --> 04:42.266
You see, Lanny and I want,

04:42.367 --> 04:46.900
nay, must have the BMX Tornado Rider.

04:46.967 --> 04:48.200
[GASPS]

04:48.266 --> 04:49.600
-I don't know what it is, either.
-[SIGHS]

04:49.667 --> 04:54.300
It's only the greatest bike
in the entire universe!

04:54.367 --> 04:55.600
How much are the bikes?

04:55.667 --> 04:57.000
Uh, 105.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.066
Each.

04:59.133 --> 05:01.233
There's no way I'm gonna buy you
a $105 bike.

05:01.300 --> 05:02.333
You understand that, right?

05:02.400 --> 05:03.767
Absolutely.

05:04.467 --> 05:06.033
Mother of mine,
which I love so much?

05:06.100 --> 05:07.467
No.

05:07.533 --> 05:08.867
You could earn the money.

05:26.934 --> 05:27.934
[JO SCOFFS]

05:29.033 --> 05:30.333
Don't give him money for that!

05:30.400 --> 05:33.166
-But it was really good.
-[SCOFFS]

05:33.233 --> 05:35.200
Mrs. Carabino, down the street,

05:35.266 --> 05:37.600
I know she could use some help
around the house.

05:37.667 --> 05:39.033
Mrs. Carabino?

05:39.100 --> 05:42.900
The one with the stuffed birds
and the bald cat?

05:46.533 --> 05:48.233
Yeah, you're right, Lanny.

05:48.300 --> 05:51.700
"Anything worth having,
is worth earning."

05:53.800 --> 05:57.200
I know, Lanny, but they like it
when you say stuff like that.

06:02.934 --> 06:04.600
-[GRUNTS AND GASPS]
-Ask me.

06:04.700 --> 06:07.333
-Ask me, ask me, ask me!
-[PANTING]

06:07.400 --> 06:09.166
-Um...
-Okay, I'll tell.

06:09.233 --> 06:11.734
Cody Pierson just asked me
to the dance.

06:11.800 --> 06:14.400
Cody Pierson? Oh, my gosh,
that's so cool.

06:15.333 --> 06:16.333
Who's Cody Pierson?

06:16.400 --> 06:18.834
You know, Cody Pierson,
he's in three of our classes,

06:18.900 --> 06:20.400
always sits in the back.

06:20.467 --> 06:22.734
Okay, I didn't know who he was either,
but that's not important.

06:22.800 --> 06:24.767
The main thing is,
I have a date for the dance.

06:24.834 --> 06:28.467
[SIGHING] Yeah, okay,
that's really cool, but, um,

06:28.533 --> 06:30.066
-I have to tell you something.
-GORDO: So...

06:30.133 --> 06:31.433
-[GASPS]
-You guys hear what happened?

06:31.500 --> 06:33.900
[GASPS] People are already
talking about me and Cody?

06:33.967 --> 06:35.200
I guess we're a couple!

06:35.266 --> 06:37.333
-[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]
-No, someone broke that statue

06:37.400 --> 06:39.433
-in front of the gym.
-The "Cut that out" guy?

06:39.500 --> 06:41.066
Who did that?

06:41.133 --> 06:44.467
Kate did it! Kate,
Kate, Kate, Kate, Kate!

06:44.567 --> 06:45.900
Did I say that?

06:45.967 --> 06:49.200
Mmm, no word yet,
but whoever did is in major trouble.

06:49.266 --> 06:50.433
-[SIGHS]
-Ooh.

06:50.533 --> 06:52.433
Uh, guys?

06:55.000 --> 06:57.533
-That's so not good.
-[MOUTHING] No.

06:57.600 --> 07:00.266
And the question is,
what are we gonna do about it?

07:00.367 --> 07:01.333
Okay.

07:01.834 --> 07:04.467
How 'bout we
smuggle you into Canada

07:04.533 --> 07:06.066
in the hold of a fishing boat.

07:06.133 --> 07:07.767
And then we
change our names,

07:07.834 --> 07:09.900
so that you can get a
job as a lumberjack.

07:09.967 --> 07:11.667
Uh, we wait
for the heat to die off,

07:11.734 --> 07:13.266
then we come back and
get you.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.333
Till then you'll be known as
FrÃ¨re Jacques.

07:16.400 --> 07:17.767
-But...
-What?

07:17.834 --> 07:19.200
I think it's a workable plan.

07:19.734 --> 07:21.333
Gordo, I didn't do it.

07:21.400 --> 07:23.500
Oh, okay, good, then, then go
with that, yeah.

07:23.934 --> 07:25.567
Great.
One head in your backpack,

07:25.633 --> 07:28.000
and suddenly your friends starts
looking at you funny.

07:28.834 --> 07:29.867
You guys don't understand.

07:29.934 --> 07:31.133
I really didn't do it.

07:31.200 --> 07:32.200
Kate did it.

07:32.433 --> 07:33.433
Oh...

07:33.500 --> 07:35.567
Oh. See, that makes a lot
more sense.

07:36.133 --> 07:37.133
Duh...

07:40.567 --> 07:42.300
Can I offer you something
to eat?

07:42.867 --> 07:44.000
Pimento loaf?

07:45.233 --> 07:46.233
Bologna rollup?

07:47.166 --> 07:48.934
Lime gelatin mold?

07:50.934 --> 07:52.500
No. Not when there's, uh,

07:52.567 --> 07:54.133
work to be done, you know?

07:54.467 --> 07:57.100
So, uh, want us to go rake
some leaves?

07:57.200 --> 07:58.200
No.

07:58.367 --> 07:59.500
Mow your lawn?

07:59.567 --> 08:00.567
No.

08:01.100 --> 08:04.800
Do something outside in the...
fresh air?

08:04.867 --> 08:06.367
No.

08:06.600 --> 08:09.600
You lucky little boys
get to clean my attic.

08:18.500 --> 08:20.700
This is gonna take forever.

08:22.900 --> 08:24.200
Guess we oughta get started.

08:24.700 --> 08:25.700
Just remember,

08:26.000 --> 08:29.033
BMX Tornado Rider.

08:30.567 --> 08:31.567
Okay.

08:37.567 --> 08:40.467
Actually, you know, that isn't
a bad look for you.

09:00.567 --> 09:02.200
Okay, Gordo what's the plan?

09:02.266 --> 09:05.000
I told you the plan.
You didn't like the plan.

09:05.066 --> 09:06.400
But you always have a plan.

09:06.467 --> 09:08.000
I did. It was Canada.

09:08.066 --> 09:09.700
Okay, I have a plan.

09:09.767 --> 09:11.734
Why don't you
just go to Principal Tweedy

09:11.800 --> 09:13.467
and tell him Kate broke it?

09:13.900 --> 09:17.033
Because middle school doesn't
have a witness protection program.

09:17.967 --> 09:20.367
All I wanted to do was
make the gym pretty for the dance,

09:20.433 --> 09:23.066
have a nice outfit, and maybe get
asked out by someone.

09:23.133 --> 09:25.500
You need to lower your
expectations.

09:25.567 --> 09:28.467
Lizzie, listen, it's not that big
of a deal.

09:28.533 --> 09:32.033
Uh, people will still go to the dance
and have a good time.

09:32.734 --> 09:34.367
Like me and Cody, for
instance.

09:34.433 --> 09:35.567
Wait, wait.

09:35.633 --> 09:37.767
I think that I'm getting...

09:38.400 --> 09:40.567
Yes! I've got a plan.

09:45.734 --> 09:46.900
My jaw hurts.

09:47.500 --> 09:49.100
All right. Let's do it.

09:52.700 --> 09:54.333
Ew. Ew!

09:59.066 --> 10:00.066
[GRUNTS]

10:09.367 --> 10:12.400
<i>Oh Canada...</i>

10:12.467 --> 10:14.600
Sorry, that... That's all I
know, anyway.

10:14.667 --> 10:16.834
I'll get you the rest of the lyrics
off the Internet.

10:17.700 --> 10:20.100
Whoever did this should get
a medal or something.

10:20.300 --> 10:22.100
That would be <i>moi.</i>

10:23.000 --> 10:24.000
Good job.

10:25.166 --> 10:27.367
How can she be so guiltless?

10:27.433 --> 10:28.433
Uh, Kate?

10:28.767 --> 10:30.800
Bragging about
knocking the head off a statue

10:30.867 --> 10:32.166
is not a good idea, okay?

10:32.233 --> 10:33.600
That's not something to be proud of.

10:33.667 --> 10:36.400
Look, if we were gonna get
busted by now, we would have.

10:39.033 --> 10:40.266
Uh-uh. "We"?

10:40.333 --> 10:41.934
How did this turn
into "we"?

10:42.000 --> 10:44.266
Did you see us talking?
Did you see us talking?

10:44.333 --> 10:45.567
Who, you and Gordo?

10:45.633 --> 10:46.834
No, me and Cody.

10:46.900 --> 10:48.367
Do you think I should wear a
skirt to the dance?

10:48.433 --> 10:49.667
Do you think Cody will like
a skirt?

10:49.734 --> 10:51.667
Miranda, I cannot help you

10:51.734 --> 10:53.500
figure out what you
want to wear to the dance right now

10:53.567 --> 10:55.400
when my stomach is in knots.

10:55.467 --> 10:57.400
Why? You... you didn't do
anything.

10:57.467 --> 11:00.033
Uh, plus, it's probably all blown
over by now.

11:00.100 --> 11:01.500
Hey, who am I?

11:01.934 --> 11:03.934
Hey, you kids, cut that out!

11:04.000 --> 11:07.066
Tudgeman. He's talking like a
statue head.

11:09.200 --> 11:11.600
Well, maybe almost blown over.

11:13.166 --> 11:14.934
PRINCIPAL TWEEDY: <i>Students, </i>
<i>please gather </i>

11:15.000 --> 11:16.767
<i>for an emergency assembly in the gym.</i>

11:16.834 --> 11:19.066
Yeah, it's all blown over.

11:19.333 --> 11:20.333
Right.

11:23.934 --> 11:25.800
I've gathered the school

11:25.867 --> 11:29.400
because there has been an
act of vandalism

11:29.467 --> 11:31.500
perpetrated in our little
community.

11:31.734 --> 11:34.467
Now, you may feel that no one
is affected, but you're wrong.

11:34.533 --> 11:36.100
And we feel

11:36.166 --> 11:39.834
that someone here
knows all about it.

11:39.900 --> 11:41.367
It was me! I did it.

11:41.433 --> 11:43.033
I've been
secretly relabeling all the

11:43.100 --> 11:45.367
labels in the science lab from
standard to metric.

11:45.433 --> 11:46.467
But I had a reason.

11:46.533 --> 11:48.900
We have to wake up, people!
The metric system is here.

11:50.600 --> 11:53.567
This wasn't about the science lab
at all, was it?

11:53.633 --> 11:54.633
No.

11:56.367 --> 11:57.400
Oh...

11:57.600 --> 12:01.333
The statue of our first principal
has been defaced.

12:02.000 --> 12:07.900
Now, until whoever has committed this
act of vandalism comes forward,

12:08.533 --> 12:11.367
the Spring Fling Dance is canceled.

12:12.266 --> 12:13.266
That is all.

12:16.567 --> 12:18.133
I didn't even do anything.

12:18.200 --> 12:20.233
So why do I feel like I'm in so
much trouble?

12:20.800 --> 12:23.233
Maybe it's because I still have
a head in my backpack.

12:25.367 --> 12:27.066
So, when are you going to tell?

12:27.367 --> 12:28.367
Um...

12:28.433 --> 12:29.800
Lizzie, you can't tell.

12:29.867 --> 12:31.433
Well, uh...

12:31.900 --> 12:33.300
She has to tell,

12:33.367 --> 12:34.967
or else the
dance will be canceled,

12:35.000 --> 12:37.066
and Cody and I will never
have our moment.

12:37.133 --> 12:38.400
Well I was go...

12:38.467 --> 12:39.600
She can't tell.

12:39.667 --> 12:42.433
If she tells, everyone in school
will know that she's a fink.

12:42.500 --> 12:43.500
A fink?

12:44.000 --> 12:46.800
You know, a rat, a stool pigeon,
a snitch.

12:46.867 --> 12:49.934
Okay, she has to tell
because of Cody.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.400
You know? Cody? A hunk, a hottie,
a heartthrob.

12:53.467 --> 12:55.433
My first dance with an actual date.

12:55.500 --> 12:57.734
Whoo-hoo! Bike time!

12:57.800 --> 13:01.834
Oh, yeah! Whoo-hoo!
Yeah!

13:02.233 --> 13:05.000
Anyway, you guys, thanks for talking
this over with me.

13:05.066 --> 13:06.533
It's helped a lot.

13:11.133 --> 13:14.967
Ladies and gentlemen, put your hands

13:15.033 --> 13:18.800
together for the BMX Tornado Rider!

13:21.000 --> 13:22.000
Cool.

13:22.633 --> 13:24.033
Well, where's yours?

13:24.100 --> 13:26.867
We only had enough money for one,
so we're gonna share.

13:26.934 --> 13:30.200
Aw, that's so sweet.
They're gonna share.

13:30.266 --> 13:31.467
That's nice, kids.

13:36.233 --> 13:37.500
You think that's gonna work?

13:37.667 --> 13:40.066
Mmm, no. Not a chance.

13:44.633 --> 13:47.000
I could be wrong
about this, Lanny, but

13:47.066 --> 13:50.266
I believe we're two of the happiest
kids in the world.

13:52.166 --> 13:55.934
No, no, no, no, no, no, Lanny,
you first.

13:56.233 --> 13:58.400
No, Lanny, I insist.

13:58.467 --> 14:01.133
You go ahead. Head butt!

14:23.867 --> 14:29.266
Hmm... I would've thought having a
bike would be more... Fun.

14:40.900 --> 14:47.066
A rat, a stool pigeon, a fink.
A rat, a stool pigeon, a fink.

14:47.166 --> 14:49.900
My first dance with an actual date.

14:49.967 --> 14:54.533
An actual date, date, date. Tell!

14:54.600 --> 14:55.600
Don't tell.

14:55.667 --> 14:56.667
Tell!

14:56.734 --> 14:58.000
Don't tell.

14:58.066 --> 15:00.300
Stop telling her to tell.

15:00.367 --> 15:01.734
You keep out of this.

15:01.800 --> 15:04.300
I'm not keeping outta this.
You keep out o' this.

15:05.133 --> 15:08.500
-Ow! Cut that out.
-Ow! You cut that out.

15:09.433 --> 15:11.266
Hey, you kids, cut that out.

15:12.266 --> 15:14.633
I gotta stop eating
right before I go to bed.

15:27.767 --> 15:28.767
Don't do it!

15:39.734 --> 15:42.266
Oh! So, did you tell?

15:42.333 --> 15:43.667
Of course she didn't tell

15:43.734 --> 15:44.734
Actually...

15:45.567 --> 15:47.700
PRINCIPAL TWEEDY: <i>Will all students </i>
<i>please report to the gym </i>

15:47.767 --> 15:49.867
<i>for an emergency assembly.</i>

15:49.934 --> 15:51.934
I hope I did the right thing.

15:58.166 --> 16:02.567
It gives me great pleasure to
announce the Spring Dance is back on!

16:04.000 --> 16:08.200
The person responsible for damaging
the statue has been identified.

16:13.166 --> 16:16.367
Apparently, looks can't kill,
because I'm still alive.

16:16.433 --> 16:19.300
Lizzie McGuire has confessed

16:19.367 --> 16:23.834
to beheading the statue of my friend
and mentor, Walter Patterson.

16:24.767 --> 16:27.700
I knew she did it. I just didn't
wanna tell on her.

16:27.767 --> 16:31.400
Of course, Miss McGuire will not be
permitted to attend the dance.

16:33.934 --> 16:34.934
Hey, Lizzie,

16:35.000 --> 16:38.433
why'd you knock the head off that,
"Hey, you kids, cut that out" guy?

16:38.500 --> 16:40.433
She didn't do it, Ethan.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.233
She wanted
everyone to go to the dance,

16:43.433 --> 16:46.734
so she said she did it,
even though she didn't.

16:53.166 --> 16:55.100
The kids are really quiet tonight.

16:58.567 --> 16:59.567
It's kinda nice.

17:00.667 --> 17:04.200
No, Sam, it's not.
Something's wrong with them.

17:05.200 --> 17:06.200
They're not fighting.

17:08.200 --> 17:10.934
All right, we'll be good parents
and we'll talk to 'em.

17:11.000 --> 17:12.000
Who first?

17:13.633 --> 17:14.633
Matt'll be easier.

17:14.700 --> 17:15.900
-Good thinking.
-Yep.

17:17.800 --> 17:21.100
Hey, Matt, honey,
is everything okay?

17:21.166 --> 17:23.000
Yeah, just fine.

17:24.367 --> 17:25.567
Bike workin' out all right?

17:25.900 --> 17:28.033
Yeah, the bike's great.

17:28.467 --> 17:30.133
You guys sharin' okay?

17:30.333 --> 17:32.033
The sharing's fine. I mean,

17:32.100 --> 17:36.000
Lanny goes and rides the bike,
then I go ride the bike.

17:36.767 --> 17:38.633
Well, what's the problem, then?

17:39.266 --> 17:43.667
